==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English, from Old French [[tribu]], from Latin [[tribus]].

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪb|-aɪb]]

=== Noun ===
'''tribe''' ([[tribes]])

# A socially, ethnically, and politically cohesive group of people.
# The collective noun for various animals.

